7.23:
Forge the chain,
for the land is filled with crimes of bloodshed,
and the city is filled with violence.

7.27:
The king will mourn;
the prince will be clothed in grief;
and the hands of the people of the land will tremble.
I will deal with them according to their own conduct,
and I will judge them by their own standards.
Then they will know that I am the Lord.

21.16:
Slash to the right;
turn to the left—
wherever your blade is directed.

24.12:
It has frustrated every effort;
its thick corrosion will not come off.
Into the fire with its corrosion!

28.17:
Your heart became proud because of your beauty;
For the sake of your splendor
you corrupted your wisdom.
So I threw you down to the ground;
I made you a spectacle before kings.

32.22:
“Assyria is there with her whole assembly;
her graves are all around her.
All of them are slain, fallen by the sword.

48.16:
These are the city’s measurements:
1½ miles on the north side;
1½ miles on the south side;
1½ miles on the east side;
and 1½ miles on the west side.
